The paper discusses a technique for summarizing large data sets using weighted samples, which is a common problem in data structures (cs.DS) and databases (cs.DB). The technique involves optimizing the summary size while maintaining statistical guarantees, which is a problem in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses applications in metric spaces, which is a topic in information retrieval (cs.IR) and similarity search (cs.SI).
